==Talking to Emem Sharma==
* '''Emem Sharma:''' I'm Emem Sharma, and I am on a mission to protect the endangered big cats of Gielinor.
* '''Emem Sharma:''' I am looking for your help to protect and rebuild four habitats each for a different species of big cat.
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|What do I need to do?}}
** '''Emem Sharma:''' There are habitats for four different types of big cat in the surrounding area.
** '''Emem Sharma:''' Each needs to be rebuilt or protected in some way to help the big cats survive.
** '''Emem Sharma:''' Investigate each of the areas to see how you can help.
** '''Emem Sharma:''' If you get stuck come back and ask me about your progress and I will steer you in the right direction.
** {{tact|previous}}
* {{topt|Tell me more about the cats}}
** '''Emem Sharma:''' Which big cats would you like to know about?
** {{topt|Lions}}
*** '''Emem Sharma:''' Lions live in prides and are the only cats to grow manes. Their habitat is south east of here.
*** '''Emem Sharma:''' The World Wildlife Fund has more information on big cats if you want to learn more.
*** '''Emem Sharma:''' Would you like to know about any other big cats?
*** {{tact|other}}
** {{topt|Tigers}}
*** '''Emem Sharma:''' Tigers, unlike many cats, are excellent swimmers. Their habitat is south west of here.
*** '''Emem Sharma:''' The World Wildlife Fund has more information on big cats if you want to learn more.
*** '''Emem Sharma:''' Would you like to know about any other big cats?
*** {{tact|other}}
** {{topt|Amur leopards}}
*** '''Emem Sharma:''' Amur leopards have different coats in winter to keep themselves warm. This coat can be up to 7cm long. Their habitat is north east of here.
*** '''Emem Sharma:''' The World Wildlife Fund has more information on big cats if you want to learn more.
*** '''Emem Sharma:''' Would you like to know about any other big cats?
*** {{tact|other}}
** {{topt|Snow leopards}}
*** '''Emem Sharma:''' Snow leopards can leap as far as fifteen meters in one go and can travel for many kilometres a night. Their habitat is north west of here.
*** '''Emem Sharma:''' The World Wildlife Fund has more information on big cats if you want to learn more.
*** '''Emem Sharma:''' Would you like to know about any other big cats?
*** {{tact|other}}
** {{topt|Change subject}}
*** {{tact|initial}}
* {{topt|What would the rewards be?}}
** '''Emem Sharma:''' For each area that you protect I will give a toy. The toy will be a cat of that area.
** '''Emem Sharma:''' There are four habitats to protect and rebuild, one for the lions, one for tigers, one for amur leopards and one for snow leopards.
** '''Emem Sharma:''' Once you have made the habitat safe for the cats in an area come and talk to me and I will give you your toy.
** {{tact|other}}
* {{topt|What is my progress?}}
** {{tcond|If there are still habitats left to protect:}}
*** {{tselect|Which cat do you want to check progress on?}}
*** {{topt|Tiger.}}
**** {{tcond|If no progress has been made in protecting the tiger habitat:}}
***** '''Emem Sharma:''' You have not yet started to protect the tiger habitat. Try talking to the dwarves south of here.
**** {{tcond|If the player has agreed to build the bridge:}}
***** '''Emem Sharma:'''  Thank you for stopping the dwarves cutting down the trees. Now you need to build the bridge to help them easily across the river.
***** '''Emem Sharma:'''  Try looking for some stone to the south.
***** {{tact|end}}
*** {{topt|Lion.}}
**** {{tcond|If no progress has been made in protecting the lion habitat:}}
***** '''Emem Sharma:''' You have not yet started to protect the lion habitat. The grasslands in their area needs regrowing. Look at some of the existing grasses to find seeds.
***** {{tact|end}}
*** {{topt|Amur Leopard.}}
**** {{tcond|If no progress has been made in protecting the amur leopard habitat:}}
***** '''Emem Sharma:''' You have not yet started to protect the amur leopard habitat. The pine trees in their area need regrowing. Look at some of the existing trees to find seeds.
***** {{tact|end}}
*** {{topt|Snow leopard.}}
**** {{tcond|If no progress has been made in protecting the snow leopard habitat:}}
***** '''Emem Sharma:''' You have not yet started to protect the snow leopard habitat. The fencing that is holding the sheep in their pen nearby needs repairing.
***** {{tact|end}}
** {{tcond|If all habitats have been protected:}}
*** '''Emem Sharma:''' You have protected the habitats of all of the different big cats. Thank you for all of your help for this worthy cause.
*** {{tact|end}}

